{
  "texts": [
    "[Per02, Section 1.3]) along the flow, computing it in two different ways.",
    "Notice that the horizontal part of the soliton vector field isX H = ∇f, so that ∂ t f t = |∇f | 2.On the one hand, we have scal m,t = scal m •η t, so the variation is ⟨∇ scal m, ∇f ⟩.",
    "(Notice that ∇ scal m is horizontal since scal m is constant on the fibres of π: M → B.)",
    "On the other hand, we can calculate using the variational formulae for geometric quantities (see [Bes87, §1.K], noting that they use the opposite sign convention for the Laplacian).",
    "Equating these gives:(28) ⟨∇ scal m, ∇f ⟩ = ∆ scal +2 Ric g + 1 2 g, Ric g + 2 ∆|∇f | 2 + 2 Hessf, Ric g + 1 2 g -2 Ric(∇f, ∇f) + |∇f | 2 + 2 ∇|∇f | 2, ∇f.Using the affine soliton equation (26), we have 2 Ric g + 1 2 g, Ric g + 4 Hessf, Ric g + 1 2 g = 2 D ad, D ad -1 2 g + 4|P | 2 + ∆f -2|Hessf | 2."
  ]
}